03/04/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Albanian Prime Minister Fatos Nano and his Macedonian counterpart, Branko Crvenkovski, met on Wednesday (2 April) within the framework of the international leadership forum in Athens.
Their talks focused on enhancing bilateral co-operation and on the opening of the new border crossing near Debar.
Crvenkovski and Nano agreed to meet again at the beginning of May.
Nano met also with Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis.
They agreed that bilteral ties have improved significantly over the past few years, particularly in the areas of economic development, social and infrastructure projects.
They also discussed future projects aimed at fighting crime and trafficking.
(Albanian Daily News, Shekulli, Koha Jone - 03/04/03;
MIA, ATA - 02/04/03)
